{{Unreferenced|date=February 2007}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Sports Hall | nickname = Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Sports Hall | image = Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Sports Hall.png | caption = | size = | location = [[Büyükdere Avenue|Büyükdere Caddesi]], Derbent Mevkisi, [[Sarıyer]], [[Istanbul]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|07|35|N|29|01|44|E|type:landmark_source:kolossus-trwiki|display=inline, title}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1995 | renovated = | owner = [[Turkish Basketball Federation|TBF]] | operator = | expanded = | surface = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Darüşşafaka Doğuş]] | construction_cost = | seating_capacity = [[Basketball]]: 3,500 }}
'''Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Sports Hall''' ([[Turkish language|Turkish]]: Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Spor Salonu) is a multi-purpose [[indoor arena]] that is located in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]. The arena is mostly used to host [[basketball]] games, but can also be used to host artistic and cultural events. It has a [[seating capacity]] for 3,500 spectators.
==History== Darüşşafaka Ayhan Şahenk Sports Hall opened in 1995, and is the home arena of the [[Turkish Basketball Super League|Turkish Super League]] team [[Darüşşafaka Doğuş]]. It was also for a while, the home arena of the Turkish Super League club [[Anadolu Efes S.K.|Anadolu Efes]]. [[Galatasaray S.K. (men's basketball)|Galatasaray men's basketball]] and [[Galatasaray S.K. (women's basketball)|Galatasaray women's basketball]] teams have also used the arena to host home games.
