The '''Town Ground''' in Rushden is a [[cricket]] ground which was used by [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club]] in  22 [[First-class cricket|first-class]] matches for 39 years between 1924 and 1963. It is now used predominantly for [[Northamptonshire Cricket League|Northamptonshire Premier League]] games, serving as the home ground of Rushden Town Cricket Club since 2003.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/718.html|title=Town Ground in Rushden|accessdate=2014-07-12|publisher=CricketArchive}}</ref>

